z^2+i=|z|
(z^2+i)^2=|z|^2
z=r\cos(\theta+i\sin\theta)
\implies |z|=r
z^2=\{r\cos(\theta+i\sin\theta)\}^2=r^2(\cos2\theta+i\sin2\theta)
r^2(\cos2\theta+i\sin2\theta)+i=r
r^2\cos2\theta=r\ \ \ \ (1)
r^2\sin2\theta+1=0 \ \ \ \ (2)
(1),
r=0
r\cos2\theta=1
r=0
(2)\implies r\cos2\theta=1\iff \cos2\theta=\frac1r
(2)\sin2\theta=-\frac1{r^2}=-\cos^22\theta=\sin^22\theta-1
\theta
\sin^22\theta-\sin2\theta-1=0
z^2 + i = |z|
(r \cos(\theta) + r i \sin(\theta))^2 + i = r
r^2\cos(2\theta) + r^2 i \sin(2\theta) + i = r
r^2 \cos(2\theta) = r
r^2 \sin(2\theta) = -1
r^4 \cos(2\theta)^2 = r^2
r^4 \sin(2\theta)^2 = 1
r^4 = r^2 + 1
